  <span id="freeText12262009550036462322" style="display:none">Twisty, well-plotted, and intriguing. Interestingly enough, the author references A Wrinkle in Time several times throughout the book, and while Madeleine L'Engle fans will certainly enjoy this time-space puzzle, the emotional depth and underlying themes aren't quite up to the same level. Still a great read for kids, though.</span>
